                            <handNote>Black letters in greenish background. Majuscule letters. Characters' size varies. Mu with the central strokes reminiscent of an upsilon on a stem and surmounted by a dot; alpha with the top bar terminating in a serif to the left; kappa with the arm terminating in a long serif; omega with its apex surmounted by a crosslet; tau with a top bar terminating in serifs at either end with its stem crossed at mid-height; TΡ, ΤΟ, ΠΗΝ joined in ligature. The ending Ν in ταπείνωσιν (line 7) is rendered with tachygraphic sign. Systematic use of accents and breathings. Breathings of the archaic variety (angular). Letter height: <height unit="cm">3</height>.
